title: For Sale/Trade:  Armslist Public Service Announcement
postcontent: Have you seen how folks will say in thier ads or email responses "these are selling for xx amount of dollars" ?  Have you also noticed that almost across the board they are way wrong.  Case in point are a few 1911's listed currently.  A quick search on another well established web site serving the entire country, shows identical new pistols, in the box, for $200 less than what they are asking and $400 less than what they say they are selling for.Another catch phrase to be on the lookout for is "These are rare, and only going to go up in value".  What this simply means is you will find many others like mine in better condition but you wont pay more for them.   Even with the facts laid out in front of them, they continue the charade that somehow someway, they will sell at thier price.    Its best to ignore these folks and their ad's but anymore I wonder if we couldnt reclaim the respectability of Armslist if we call these people out, as I have chosen to do today, not by name at this point, but they will know who they are.
